The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks as controllers for safety-critical systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the challenge of certifying the correctness of neural networks, which is a problem in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed framework involves using over-approximation to reduce the size of the network, which is a technique commonly used in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the integration of the proposed framework with existing verification techniques, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
